The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
      Boy critical after road mishap    Sandip Ghosh, 13, was critically injured on Friday afternoon when an autorickshaw rammed into the stationary car he was sitting in near the Lokenath temple on Beleghata Main Road. Police said auto driver Uttam Sen had lost control of his vehicle. Sandip, a resident of Phoolbagan, was sitting on the rear seat. He was taken to a private hospital where his condition was stated to be critical. The auto driver, too, was injured.			   Kali puja trains			   Eastern Railway will run four extra pairs of locals for Kali puja (October 17-18) to ease passenger rush. From Sealdah, one pair of locals each will run to Ranaghat, Barasat, Dankuni and Baruipur. The trains for Ranaghat, Barasat, Dankuni and Baruipur will leave Sealdah at 12.40am, 12.10am, 11.20pm and 12,30am, respectively.			   Cracker haul			   Police seized 700kg firecrackers from the Sealdanga area of Dasnagar in Howrah on Friday afternoon. No one has been arrested.			   Factory fire			   A fire broke out in the production unit of a match factory at Belghoria on Friday morning. Four fire tenders controlled the blaze within an hour. Fire department officials said the blaze might have started from a container where combustible chemicals used for making match heads are mixed.			   Malaysia flight			   Air Asia announced daily direct flights between Calcutta and the Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpur from November for an all-inclusive promotional fair of Rs 1,499. The special one-way fare can be booked   till October 20, 2009, for the travel period November 19, 2009 to July 31, 2010.			   Central board		   The Union ministry of culture has selected Calcutta University vice-chancellor Suranjan Das and Partha Chatterjee, of the Centre for Studies in Social Sciences, as members of the Centres Archival Advisory Board. The tenure of the membership is three years.                                                                                                                                                                     
